2001.definition: [ἐπισχύω] from {{G1909}} and {{G2480}}; to avail further, i.e. (figuratively) insist stoutly

2002.definition: [ἐπισωρεύω] from {{G1909}} and {{G4987}}; to accumulate further, i.e. (figuratively) seek additionally

2003.definition: [ἐπιταγή] from {{G2004}}; an injunction or decree; by implication, authoritativeness

2004.definition: [ἐπιτάσσω] from {{G1909}} and {{G5021}}; to arrange upon, i.e. order

2005.definition: [ἐπιτελέω] from {{G1909}} and {{G5055}}; to fulfill further (or completely), i.e. execute; by implication, to terminate, undergo

2006.definition: [ἐπιτήδειος] from ἐπιτηδές (enough); serviceable, i.e. (by implication) requisite

2007.definition: [ἐπιτίθημι] from {{G1909}} and {{G5087}}; to impose (in a friendly or hostile sense)

2008.definition: [ἐπιτιμάω] from {{G1909}} and {{G5091}}; to tax upon, i.e. censure or admonish; by implication, forbid

2009.definition: [ἐπιτιμία] from a compound of {{G1909}} and {{G5092}}; properly, esteem, i.e. citizenship; used (in the sense of {{G2008}}) of a penalty

2010.definition: [ἐπιτρέπω] from {{G1909}} and the base of {{G5157}}; to turn over (transfer), i.e. allow

2011.definition: [ἐπιτροπή] from {{G2010}}; permission, i.e. (by implication) full power

2012.definition: [ἐπίτροπος] from {{G1909}} and {{G5158}} (in the sense of {{G2011}}); a commissioner, i.e. domestic manager, guardian

2013.definition: [ἐπιτυγχάνω] from {{G1909}} and {{G5177}}; to chance upon, i.e. (by implication) to attain

2014.definition: [ἐπιφαίνω] from {{G1909}} and {{G5316}}; to shine upon, i.e. become (literally) visible or (figuratively) known

2015.definition: [ἐπιφάνεια] from {{G2016}}; a manifestation, i.e. (specially) the advent of Christ (past or future)

2018.definition: [ἐπιφέρω] from {{G1909}} and {{G5342}}; to bear upon (or further), i.e. adduce (personally or judicially (accuse, inflict)), superinduce

2019.definition: [ἐπιφωνέω] from {{G1909}} and {{G5455}}; to call at something, i.e. exclaim

2020.definition: [ἐπιφώσκω] a form of {{G2017}}; to begin to grow light

2021.definition: [ἐπιχειρέω] from {{G1909}} and {{G5495}}; to put the hand upon, i.e. undertake

2023.definition: [ἐπιχορηγέω] from {{G1909}} and {{G5524}}; to furnish besides, i.e. fully supply, (figuratively) aid or contribute

2026.definition: [ἐποικοδομέω] from {{G1909}} and {{G3618}}; to build upon, i.e. (figuratively) to rear up

2027.definition: [ἐποκέλλω] from {{G1909}} and ὀκέλλω (to urge); to drive upon the shore, i.e. to beach a vessel

2028.definition: [ἐπονομάζω] from {{G1909}} and {{G3687}}; to name further, i.e. denominate

2029.definition: [ἐποπτεύω] from {{G1909}} and a derivative of {{G3700}}; to inspect, i.e. watch

2030.definition: [ἐπόπτης] from {{G1909}} and a presumed derivative of {{G3700}}; a looker-on

2035.definition: [ἑπτακισχίλιοι] from {{G2034}} and {{G5507}}; seven times a thousand

2036.definition: [ἔπω] a primary verb (used only in the definite past tense, the others being borrowed from {{G2046}}, {{G4483}}, and {{G5346}}); to speak or say (by word or writing) Compare {{G3004}}.

2037.definition: [Ἔραστος] from ἐράω (to love); beloved; Erastus, a Christian

2038.definition: [ἐργάζομαι] middle voice from {{G2041}}; to toil (as a task, occupation, etc.), (by implication) effect, be engaged in or with, etc.

2039.definition: [ἐργασία] from {{G2040}}; occupation; by implication, profit, pains

2040.definition: [ἐργάτης] from {{G2041}}; a toiler; figuratively, a teacher

2041.definition: [ἔργον] from a primary (but obsolete) ἔργω (to work); toil (as an effort or occupation); by implication, an act

2042.definition: [ἐρεθίζω] from a presumed prolonged form of {{G2054}}; to stimulate (especially to anger)

2043.definition: [ἐρείδω] of obscure affinity; to prop, i.e. (reflexively) get fast

2044.definition: [ἐρεύγομαι] of uncertain affinity; to belch, i.e. (figuratively) to speak out

2045.definition: [ἐρευνάω] apparently from {{G2046}} (through the idea of inquiry); to seek, i.e. (figuratively) to investigate

2046.definition: [ἐρέω] probably a fuller form of {{G4483}}; an alternate for {{G2036}} in certain tenses; to utter, i.e. speak or say

2048.definition: [ἔρημος] of uncertain affinity; lonesome, i.e. (by implication) waste (usually as a noun, {{G5561}} being implied)

2049.definition: [ἐρημόω] from {{G2048}}; to lay waste (literally or figuratively)

2052.definition: [ἐριθεία] perhaps as the same as {{G2042}}; properly, intrigue, i.e. (by implication) faction

2054.definition: [ἔρις] of uncertain affinity; a quarrel, i.e. (by implication) wrangling

2055.definition: [ἐρίφιον] from {{G2056}}; a kidling, i.e. (genitive case) goat (symbolically, wicked person)

2056.definition: [ἔριφος] perhaps from the same as {{G2053}} (through the idea of hairiness); a kid or (genitive case) goat

2059.definition: [ἑρμηνεύω] from a presumed derivative of {{G2060}} (as the god of language); to translate

2060.definition: [Ἑρμῆς] perhaps from {{G2046}}; Hermes, the name of the messenger of the Greek deities; also of a Christian

2061.definition: [Ἑρμογένης] from {{G2060}} and {{G1096}}; born of Hermes; Hermogenes, an apostate Christian

2062.definition: [ἑρπετόν] neuter of a derivative of ἕρπω (to creep); a reptile, i.e. (by Hebraism (compare {{H7431}})) a small animal

2063.definition: [ἐρυθρός] of uncertain affinity; red, i.e. (with {{G2281}}) the Red Sea

2064.definition: [ἔρχομαι] middle voice of a primary verb  (used only in the present and imperfect tenses, the others being  supplied by a kindred (middle voice)             ἐλεύθομαι,    or (active)      ἔλθω,        which do not otherwise occur); to come or go (in a great variety of applications, literally and  figuratively)

2065.definition: [ἐρωτάω] apparently from {{G2046}} (compare {{G2045}}); to interrogate; by implication, to request Compare {{G4441}}.

2068.definition: [ἐσθίω] strengthened for a primary ἔδω (to eat); used only in certain tenses, the rest being supplied by {{G5315}}; to eat (usually literal)

2069.definition: [Ἐσλί] of Hebrew origin (probably for {{H454}}); Esli, an Israelite

2070.definition: [ἐσμέν] first person plural indicative of {{G1510}}; we are

2072.definition: [ἔσοπτρον] from {{G1519}} and a presumed derivative of {{G3700}}; a mirror (for looking into) Compare {{G2734}}.

2073.definition: [ἑσπέρα] feminine of an adjective hesperos (evening); the eve ({{G5610}} being implied)

2074.definition: [Ἐσρώμ] of Hebrew origin ({{H2696}}); Esrom (i.e. Chetsron), an Israelite

2075.definition: [ἐστέ] second person plural present indicative of {{G1510}}; ye are

2076.definition: [ἐστί] third person singular present indicative of {{G1510}}; he (she or it) is; also (with neuter plural) they are

2077.definition: [ἔστω] second person singular present imperative of {{G1510}}; be thou;  also  ἔστωσαν, third person of the same; let them be

2078.definition: [ἔσχατος] a superlative probably from {{G2192}} (in the sense of contiguity); farthest, final (of place or time)

2079.definition: [ἐσχάτως] adverb from {{G2078}}; finally, i.e. (with {{G2192}}) at the extremity of life

2081.definition: [ἔσωθεν] from {{G2080}}; from inside; also used as equivalent to {{G2080}} (inside)

2084.definition: [ἑτερόγλωσσος] from {{G2087}} and {{G1100}}; other- tongued, i.e. a foreigner

2086.definition: [ἑτεροζυγέω] from a compound of {{G2087}} and {{G2218}}; to yoke up differently, i.e. (figuratively) to associate discordantly

2087.definition: [ἕτερος] of uncertain affinity; (an-, the) other or different

2089.definition: [ἔτι] perhaps akin to {{G2094}}; "yet," still (of time or degree)

2092.definition: [ἕτοιμος] from an old noun ἐτεός (fitness); adjusted, i.e. ready

2094.definition: [ἔτος] apparently a primary word; a year

2095.definition: [εὖ] neuter of a primary εὖς (good); (adverbially) well

2096.definition: [Εὖα] of Hebrew origin ({{H2332}}); Eua (or Eva, i.e. Chavvah), the first woman

2097.definition: [εὐαγγελίζω] from {{G2095}} and {{G32}}; to announce good news ("evangelize") especially the gospel

2098.definition: [εὐαγγέλιον] from the same as {{G2097}}; a good message, i.e. the gospel

2099.definition: [εὐαγγελιστής] from {{G2097}}; a preacher of the gospel
